Great. I'm ready. Let's do it.

18:08.840 --> 18:10.888
- Right away?
- Yes.

18:11.360 --> 18:12.566
Oh, okay.

18:19.080 --> 18:21.208
First of all, I am happy to inform you

18:21.280 --> 18:24.124
that all our plans
are running smoothly and on time.

18:24.200 --> 18:26.202
Great. Can I see the flyers?

18:26.240 --> 18:28.607
Flyers are not here yet.

18:28.680 --> 18:31.490
They are at the printers.
We are trying to get them.

18:31.600 --> 18:34.046
Okay. How about the T-shirts?

18:34.080 --> 18:35.127
They are at the warehouse.

18:35.200 --> 18:37.328
We are trying to get them, too.

18:38.400 --> 18:40.323
Okay, but the equipment
that we sent over,

18:40.360 --> 18:43.807
the batting cages, balls, bats,
that's all here?

18:43.880 --> 18:48.044
I'm happy to confirm that
they all are here in India.

18:48.840 --> 18:51.810
But you don't have them here?

18:52.040 --> 18:53.883
No. They are at the customs.

18:53.920 --> 18:56.605
I think we should be working on that.

18:56.680 --> 19:01.402
Okay, Vivek, I need things
to run on time and smoothly,

19:01.440 --> 19:03.681
but actually run on time and smoothly,

19:03.720 --> 19:06.291
not Indian on time and smoothly.

19:06.360 --> 19:07.885
You know, here in India, we do things

19:08.000 --> 19:10.401
a little differently than in the US.

19:13.960 --> 19:15.485
Okay, so,

19:16.720 --> 19:18.927
what do we have to do to get our stuff?

19:20.360 --> 19:22.124
Uh, we have to pay money.

19:22.880 --> 19:25.690
Pay money. Like a bribe?

19:25.760 --> 19:28.764
No, no, no. Not a... Not a bribe.

19:28.840 --> 19:30.763
I mean, why use such words?

19:30.840 --> 19:32.604
We call it "bypassing the system."

19:32.760 --> 19:37.561
The systems in India are very slow,
so we bypass them.

19:37.600 --> 19:40.729
- By paying money.
- That's the Indian way.

19:40.760 --> 19:43.604
Indians love honking
and bypassing the system.

19:44.680 --> 19:45.841
Okay.

19:47.320 --> 19:48.446
Let's do it.

19:54.960 --> 19:56.405
He says come after three weeks.

19:56.440 --> 19:58.329
What do you want? You want more?

19:58.400 --> 20:00.129
How much do you want?

20:00.160 --> 20:01.605
Get lost!

20:01.720 --> 20:04.121
Vivek, explain to me why
we can't bypass that guy.

20:04.200 --> 20:06.407
We can, but not in there, JB.

20:06.440 --> 20:10.001
- All right, well, where?
- Ah. Well, I don't know yet.

20:10.080 --> 20:11.286
You know what, Vivek,

20:11.360 --> 20:13.283
I'm starting to lose patience
with this whole plan of yours.

20:13.320 --> 20:16.290
Don't lose patience, JB.
You are going to need it in India.

20:18.200 --> 20:19.804
Ah, here he is.

20:26.320 --> 20:27.765
He says he'll do it here!

20:27.800 --> 20:29.609
Here? In the middle of the street?

20:29.640 --> 20:32.371
That's where he wants
to bypass the system. Really?

20:38.400 --> 20:39.526
Thank you.

20:46.960 --> 20:48.485
Hey. What's up?

20:48.600 --> 20:51.331
- I found our scout.
- Really? Who?

20:51.400 --> 20:53.880
Ray Poitevint. He's one of the best.

20:53.960 --> 20:56.930
He's retired, but House says
he can be there in two weeks.

20:57.000 --> 21:00.129
- Oh, that's great. Great news.
- You're welcome.

21:00.160 --> 21:02.208
All right, listen, I'll call you tomorrow.

21:02.320 --> 21:04.527
<i>All right, I'll see you later.</i>

21:04.560 --> 21:06.369
- Bye.
- Excuse me, sir.

21:06.440 --> 21:09.649
- Are you JB Bernstein?
- Yes, I am.

21:09.680 --> 21:11.728
Hello, sir. I am Amit Rohan.

21:11.800 --> 21:13.370
I love baseball.

21:13.440 --> 21:16.040
I would like very much to work with you
on The <i>Million</i> Dollar Arm.

21:16.080 --> 21:19.050
Great. Tryouts in Mumbai
are at the end of the month.

21:19.080 --> 21:20.366
Come on by.

21:23.080 --> 21:24.366
Lobby, sir.

21:24.440 --> 21:26.966
JB sir, I don't play baseball.

21:27.040 --> 21:29.088
Look at me. Too small to compete.

21:29.160 --> 21:31.208
But I teach baseball in New Mumbai.

21:31.240 --> 21:32.366
- You do?
- Yes, sir.

21:32.400 --> 21:34.243
At my college I have seven students.

21:34.320 --> 21:36.163
Ask me any question
about the game of baseball,

21:36.200 --> 21:38.202
I will tell you. Ask me.

21:38.280 --> 21:39.566
Okay.

21:39.600 --> 21:40.806
How many innings
does a starting pitcher

21:40.880 --> 21:42.245
have to pitch to get the win?

21:45.280 --> 21:46.566
Can you ask me a different question?

21:46.640 --> 21:47.721
No. Goodbye.

21:47.760 --> 21:49.364
Sir. Sir, I'll work for free, sir.

21:52.560 --> 21:53.641
Really?

21:54.560 --> 21:56.403
Yes, sir. I'll work for free.

21:57.120 --> 21:59.282
- When can you start?
- Now, sir.

22:02.040 --> 22:03.485
Now is good. Let's go.

22:03.560 --> 22:04.766
- Really, sir?
- Yes.

22:04.800 --> 22:06.484
- Come.
- After you, please.

22:06.560 --> 22:09.291
Thank you. Thank you, JB sir. Thank
you for this life-changing opportunity.

22:09.360 --> 22:11.362
Don't sweat it. Vivek, this is Amit.

22:11.400 --> 22:12.731
He's gonna be working with us today.

22:12.760 --> 22:13.761
Hello. Amit.

22:13.840 --> 22:14.966
All right, boys, let's go.
We got a big day.

22:15.040 --> 22:16.883
- We gotta spread the word.
- Don't worry, JB.

22:16.920 --> 22:19.605
Indians are very good
at spreading the word.

22:22.000 --> 22:23.331
<i>An American company</i>

22:23.400 --> 22:26.449
<i>is hoping to find a cricketer
to throw a very fast ball.</i>

22:26.520 --> 22:28.045
The prize is worth one hundred...

22:28.080 --> 22:29.491
...thousand US dollars...

22:29.560 --> 22:31.801
...with the chance to win $1 million.

22:35.760 --> 22:37.649
But do you think in a <i>country like India,</i>

22:37.720 --> 22:39.131
where we're obsessed with cricket,

22:39.200 --> 22:41.567
do you really think American
baseball will catch on?

22:58.760 --> 23:01.445
You're sure we don't need a written
contract for the TV studio?

23:01.480 --> 23:02.811
It won't be necessary, JB.

23:02.840 --> 23:05.320
That just seems crazy
to me, even for here.

23:05.360 --> 23:07.681
The TV studios will be there, trust me.

23:08.520 --> 23:10.488
You see, Vivek, in the US,

23:10.560 --> 23:13.166
we would get lawyers
and write up contracts,

23:13.240 --> 23:14.651
and then everything would run smoothly.

23:14.680 --> 23:16.728
But do lawyers and contracts

23:16.800 --> 23:18.848
make things run smoothly in the US?

23:18.920 --> 23:21.082
No, they generally
just confuse the hell out of everything.

23:21.160 --> 23:22.525
But it might make me feel better.

23:22.600 --> 23:23.647
I understand.

23:24.840 --> 23:27.650
JB sir, the Major League
Baseball scout Mr. Ray has arrived.

23:27.720 --> 23:28.881
He is in the taxi.

23:28.960 --> 23:32.009
I went to the airport
to pick him up. It's really exciting.

23:32.040 --> 23:34.008
Fantastic. Bring him up.

23:37.360 --> 23:39.044
We cannot do this.

23:43.080 --> 23:44.161
Ray-

23:45.840 --> 23:46.921
Ray!

23:49.560 --> 23:50.971
Is he breathing?

23:52.720 --> 23:54.563
Yes. Should I take him
to the hospital, sir?

23:54.640 --> 23:56.244
No, no. Hold on a minute.

23:57.320 --> 23:58.446
Hey-

23:58.960 --> 24:00.325
Am I on fire?

24:01.360 --> 24:03.249
No. Sorry about that.

24:03.840 --> 24:05.569
That better be filtered water.

24:06.920 --> 24:09.366
- Who are you?
- I'm JB Bernstein.

24:09.400 --> 24:12.244
- Oh, the agent.
- Yes, the agent.

24:13.040 --> 24:16.089
- Am I in India?
- Yes, yes, India. India, sir.

24:16.160 --> 24:18.970
- They have hotels in India?
- Yes, they do.

24:19.040 --> 24:21.327
Take me to a hotel
and don't wake me up again

24:21.360 --> 24:23.966
until somebody's throwing
a baseball, you got that?

24:24.920 --> 24:28.003
All right, well,
I just wanna say it's nice to meet you,

24:28.040 --> 24:30.168
and get ready, 'cause we're on the road

24:30.200 --> 24:31.565
first thing in the morning, okay?

24:31.600 --> 24:32.886
I can't wait.

24:37.640 --> 24:39.847
- Just take him to the hotel.
- Okay, sir.

24:56.160 --> 24:58.242
All right, today we're in Nashik.

24:58.280 --> 24:59.725
- Nas-hik.
- Nas-hik.

24:59.760 --> 25:02.650
Tomorrow Jaipur, New Delhi,
up to Chandigarh,

25:02.720 --> 25:05.041
then we are in Lucknow, Kolkata,

25:05.080 --> 25:07.924
Bangalore, Goa, then back
to Mumbai for the final.

25:08.000 --> 25:11.129
- How's that sound, Ray?
- Sounds wonderful.

25:11.200 --> 25:13.601
- Are those places?
- They are indeed.

25:13.640 --> 25:14.846
You like being on the road?

25:17.440 --> 25:18.521
Words cannot express.

25:31.160 --> 25:33.527
- They all here for us?
- Yes, JB.

25:36.000 --> 25:37.968
This is awesome.

26:01.480 --> 26:03.323
Things are running very smoothly, JB.

26:03.360 --> 26:04.521
I guess they are.

26:04.600 --> 26:07.046
- This is great.
- We'll see.

26:48.440 --> 26:50.800
Vivek, we've been here half a
day. No one can throw over 45.

26:51.920 --> 26:54.287
JB sir, another 60 men just signed up.

26:54.360 --> 26:55.441
Great.

26:55.520 --> 26:56.760
Ray, how are you gonna
know if anyone can throw

26:56.840 --> 26:58.046
if you keep your eyes shut all day?

26:58.080 --> 26:59.730
- I can hear it.
- Really?

26:59.760 --> 27:01.524
Yeah.

27:01.560 --> 27:03.050
That was about a 43.

27:05.560 --> 27:06.925
<i>In an impressive turnout</i>

27:07.000 --> 27:08.120
<i>in the city of Nashik today,</i>

27:09.320 --> 27:10.924
<i>Hundreds of young
contestants showed up</i>

27:11.000 --> 27:12.764
<i>to try out for the US-based</i>

27:12.840 --> 27:15.161
<i>Million Dollar Arm pitching contest,</i>

27:15.200 --> 27:17.362
<i>which continues to travel across India</i>

27:17.400 --> 27:19.607
<i>in search of a few strong-armed boys.</i>

27:19.720 --> 27:22.690
<i>Today's contestants
showed exceptional enthusiasm</i>

27:22.720 --> 27:24.563
<i>for a sport which they have likely...</i>

27:24.600 --> 27:26.728
Oh, God, what did I eat?

27:26.760 --> 27:28.888
<i>And yet, despite the massive turnout,</i>

27:29.000 --> 27:30.889
<i>it seems to be harder than it looks.</i>

27:38.400 --> 27:40.243
- Hey. <i>Hello?</i>
- Hi, Brenda.

27:40.280 --> 27:42.487
<i>Look, we're skyping. How's India?</i>

27:43.960 --> 27:46.964
It's fine. I'm in the middle
of something. What's up?

27:47.040 --> 27:49.964
<i>I'm sorry. So I don't
mean to be the bearer of bad tidings,</i>

27:50.040 --> 27:52.884
<i>but your washing machine
has broken now, too.</i>

27:52.920 --> 27:55.730
<i>- Seriously?
- I am just gonna pay for it,</i>

27:55.760 --> 27:58.331
<i>- and I'll deduct it out of my rent.
- Fine. Do that.</i>

27:58.400 --> 28:01.370
<i>So how's the contest going?
Are you excited?</i>

28:01.440 --> 28:04.011
I will be if we can
find a kid who can pitch in the 80s.

28:04.080 --> 28:05.923
In... Okay.

28:05.960 --> 28:08.440
<i>Um, how's the food? Is it crazy good?</i>

28:10.800 --> 28:12.160
I should get back to work, Brenda.

28:12.200 --> 28:14.726
<i>Okay. Good luck with the...</i>

28:14.760 --> 28:17.161
- Okay. Bye.
- Bye.

28:53.640 --> 28:54.766
So many people there.

29:53.760 --> 29:56.411
JB sir, he is saying he is young in spirit.

29:56.520 --> 29:57.726
He wants to try.

29:58.040 --> 30:00.042
- Huh?

30:14.680 --> 30:16.250
What is that, son?

30:17.680 --> 30:19.011
Million Dollar Arm.

30:19.200 --> 30:20.884
You don't play cricket.

30:20.920 --> 30:22.729
It's a contest.

30:22.840 --> 30:25.764
One million US dollars.

30:26.800 --> 30:28.086
This is for kids.

30:28.800 --> 30:30.928
You have work to do.

30:30.960 --> 30:33.042
Real work.

30:44.240 --> 30:46.527
<i>Calling all cricket players!</i>

30:46.600 --> 30:50.321
<i>Come and be a contestant in the
"Million Dollar Arm" contest.</i>

30:50.400 --> 30:51.925
Coach?

30:52.000 --> 30:53.286
What is it, Rinku?

30:53.320 --> 30:57.041
We're all track and field,
not cricket players.

30:57.120 --> 31:04.083
Just because they are calling for cricket
players doesn't mean you can't try out.

31:06.040 --> 31:08.611
I want to sign up, Coach.

31:08.640 --> 31:10.290
So then sign up.

31:10.360 --> 31:12.362
I'm not your secretary, Rinku.

31:13.480 --> 31:17.405
If I won a million dollars,
I bet you would be.

31:17.920 --> 31:20.764
You make a funny joke.

31:21.200 --> 31:23.202
Everyone! 10 laps!

31:23.600 --> 31:24.601
Get up!

31:24.720 --> 31:26.927
Courtesy of Mr. Singh.

31:28.040 --> 31:29.565
This is a total disaster.

31:29.800 --> 31:31.962
Oh, come on, it's not that bad.

31:32.000 --> 31:34.287
Not one of these kids can
throw over 65 miles an hour.

31:34.320 --> 31:36.448
I swear to God, some of 'em
can't even hit the cage.

31:36.480 --> 31:38.050
How's our money holding out?

31:38.120 --> 31:39.121
Well, it's not, but you know what,

31:39.160 --> 31:40.650
don't worry about that. You find our boys

31:40.680 --> 31:43.968
and I will figure out a way
to make the budget work.

31:44.000 --> 31:45.161
What does Ray think?

31:45.200 --> 31:46.690
<i>Well, when he wakes up,
I'll ask him. By the way,</i>

31:46.760 --> 31:48.444
do you think you could
have gotten someone

31:48.480 --> 31:50.005
a little more of this century?

31:50.080 --> 31:52.048
<i>Hey, the price was right, all right?</i>

31:52.120 --> 31:53.565
So stop your complaining.

31:53.680 --> 31:55.250
Where are you?
What city are you in, anyway?

31:55.320 --> 31:57.800
- I'm in Agra.
- Agra? Wait.

31:57.840 --> 31:59.888
That's where the Taj Mahal is, right?

32:00.360 --> 32:02.283
Yeah, no, I'm standing
right in front of it.

32:02.320 --> 32:04.607
<i>- How is it?
- It</i> is <i>white.</i>

32:04.680 --> 32:06.648
Except for the part that's red.

32:06.680 --> 32:08.045
There's a little dog in the foreground.

32:08.120 --> 32:09.804
Come on, man. Seriously,
how is the Taj Mahal?

32:09.840 --> 32:11.080
I've always wanted to see it.

32:11.160 --> 32:14.767
Oh, well, tell you what. Why don't I put
your friend Ray on the phone

32:14.840 --> 32:17.002
and he can give you
his first impressions?

32:18.360 --> 32:20.169
<i>Ray, buddy, how are you?</i>

32:20.840 --> 32:22.524
<i>Hello? Ray?</i>

32:33.600 --> 32:34.840
<i>Sell your friend for cash!</i>

32:38.640 --> 32:41.211
- Hi, Brenda.
- Hey. <i>Hey,</i> JB.

32:41.280 --> 32:43.851
<i>I have some very good news for you.</i>

32:43.880 --> 32:46.884
<i>The repairman came and he fixed
both of our washing machines.</i>

32:46.920 --> 32:48.445
<i>Two for the price of one. Done.</i>

32:48.520 --> 32:50.488
Really? How'd you swing that?

32:50.560 --> 32:53.450
<i>- I slept with him.
- Seriously?</i>

32:53.760 --> 32:56.570
<i>No. But he was
very attractive, I'll give him that.</i>

32:56.600 --> 32:59.683
<i>- How is the contest going?
- Not great.</i>

33:00.320 --> 33:02.243
No one over here can throw a baseball.

33:02.360 --> 33:03.885
<i>Don't worry about it.
You're gonna find your guy,</i>

33:04.040 --> 33:05.769
<i>and then you're gonna
be back here before you know it</i>

33:05.840 --> 33:07.569
<i>regaling a whole new crop of models</i>

33:07.600 --> 33:09.443
<i>to tell your fabulous stories to.</i>

33:09.520 --> 33:10.521
Thanks for the pep talk.

33:10.560 --> 33:13.040
<i>All right, I'm gonna jump in the shower
'cause I got a date tonight.</i>

33:13.080 --> 33:14.445
Really? With who?

33:15.400 --> 33:17.721
<i>- Uh, I'm not gonna tell you.
- Come on.</i>

33:17.760 --> 33:20.240
<i>Fine, the Maytag man. Bye, India.</i>

33:42.080 --> 33:44.048
This place looks like it has potential.

33:44.120 --> 33:47.761
This is Lucknow.
It has a very fine reputation.

33:47.800 --> 33:53.011
Reputation? Good.
Anything related to sports?

33:53.080 --> 33:55.970
Yes, boys from
all over India come here for training.

33:56.000 --> 33:57.968
Well, then there should
be a few qualifiers.

33:58.000 --> 33:59.411
What do you think, Ray? You feeling it?

33:59.440 --> 34:01.124
I'm feeling something.

34:01.160 --> 34:03.811
I think it's the dinner I had last night.

34:03.880 --> 34:05.882
Been there. Brutal.

34:16.600 --> 34:19.922
All right, all right,
we got a couple of contenders here.

34:20.320 --> 34:22.800
<i>One, welsh.</i>

34:23.560 --> 34:25.244
They were all crap.

34:25.320 --> 34:27.004
Thanks, Ray. That's really helpful.

34:27.080 --> 34:28.081
You want me to lie?

34:28.159 --> 34:31.004
I do. I kind of want you
to lie, a little bit.

34:33.000 --> 34:34.206
That sounded good.

34:39.159 --> 34:40.321
Did he just throw 83?

34:40.360 --> 34:43.125
Sure sounded like it.
Let's see if he can do it again.

34:54.840 --> 34:56.170
- Wow!
- Whoa.

34:58.680 --> 35:00.364
Okay. You know what we call that?

35:00.720 --> 35:03.121
- Manslaughter.
- No, we call that juice.

35:03.200 --> 35:05.362
What? You want juice? I'll get it.

35:10.280 --> 35:11.520
No, we just found one kid,

35:11.560 --> 35:12.920
threw four pitches in the mid-80s.

35:13.320 --> 35:15.687
Yeah, he's a little Wild, but I'll take it.

35:15.800 --> 35:18.087
- First time I've seen Ray's smile.
- Bernstein.

35:18.320 --> 35:19.890
- What?
- Check this out.

35:20.120 --> 35:23.522
All right, hold on.
I'll call you back. What?

35:27.440 --> 35:28.965
How long's he been like that?

35:29.200 --> 35:30.804
About a minute.

35:30.880 --> 35:32.564
Is he gonna throw?

35:32.600 --> 35:34.170
I have no idea.

35:44.560 --> 35:46.961
Is that right? 82 with that
motion? Is that even possible?

35:47.080 --> 35:49.162
A lefty with juice.
You don't see that every day.

35:49.240 --> 35:51.208
A lefty with juice is good, sir?

35:51.240 --> 35:53.720
Lefty with juice is great, Amit.

35:53.800 --> 35:56.565
A lefty with juice is money in the bank.

36:00.920 --> 36:02.684
<i>Lucknow was huge for us.</i>

36:02.760 --> 36:05.286
<i>We found four guys there,
and then we got on a roll.</i>

36:05.400 --> 36:08.768
<i>By the time we got to Goa,
we had somehow found 16 more.</i>

36:08.840 --> 36:10.649
<i>I mean, half these kids
never traveled before,</i>

36:10.720 --> 36:12.563
<i>so they were thrilled to come to Mumbai</i>

36:12.600 --> 36:13.931
<i>and train for the finals.</i>

36:14.000 --> 36:15.764
<i>We put them up in a small college</i>

36:15.840 --> 36:17.888
<i>where Amit teaches. Amit hooked it up.</i>

36:17.920 --> 36:21.083
<i>He's been key, 'cause none of these
guys really speak English.</i>

36:21.120 --> 36:22.610
<i>In fact, I asked him to come to the US</i>

36:22.640 --> 36:25.166
<i>and be the translator for the winners.</i>

36:25.240 --> 36:26.969
<i>Ray has graciously offered to stay</i>

36:27.040 --> 36:28.724
<i>and train the boys for the final.</i>

36:28.760 --> 36:30.360
<i>He actually seems to be
enjoying himself.</i>

36:30.400 --> 36:33.051
<i>And Amit has become Ray's protege,</i>

36:33.120 --> 36:37.250
<i>studying all his methods, good and bad.</i>

36:37.440 --> 36:39.169
<i>Hmm. Sounds great.</i>

36:40.880 --> 36:42.405
I don't know if it's great,

36:42.440 --> 36:43.771
but at least it's coming together.

36:43.800 --> 36:46.371
What? JB, you're in Mumbai.

